{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>Coiled-coil domain-containing protein 8 (CCDC8) is a widely expressed protein [[cite:PUB00060564]]. It is phosphorylated upon DNA damage, probably by ATM or ATR [[cite:PUB00044404], [cite:PUB00060734]]. It is a core component of the 3M complex, a complex required to regulate microtubule dynamics and genome integrity. It is unclear how the 3M complex regulates microtubules, it could act by controlling the level of a microtubule stabilizer [[cite:PUB00075113], [cite:PUB00075111]]. CCDC8 is also required for localization of CUL7 to the centrosome [[cite:PUB00075111]].</p>\n\n<p>Defects in CCDC8 are the cause of 3M syndrome type 3 (3M3), a disorder characterised by poor postnatal growth and distinctive facial features, including triangular facies, frontal bossing, fleshy tipped nose, and fleshy lips. Other features may include skeletal anomalies and prominent heels [[cite:PUB00060564]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"panther" {"PTHR47741" "COILED COIL DOMAIN-CONTAINING PROTEIN 8, CCDC8"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Coiled-coil domain-containing protein 8", "short" "Coiled-coil_p8"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 0, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 122, "taxa" 653, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 212, "sets" 0, "proteins" 212, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 121}, "pathways" 2}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR026526", :literature {"PUB00060564" {"URL" nil, "issue" "1", "authors" ["Hanson D" "Murray PG" "O'Sullivan J" "Urquhart J" "Daly S" "Bhaskar SS" "Biesecker LG" "Skae M" "Smith C" "Cole T" "Kirk J" "Chandler K" "Kingston H" "Donnai D" "Clayton PE" "Black GC."], "ISO_journal" "Am. J. Hum. Genet.", "DOI_URL" "http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.ajhg.2011.05.028", "medline_journal" "Am J Hum Genet", "t